        I have been working mostly on Backend, but I like to identify myself
        with a
        <a
          href="https://medium.com/quick-code/what-it-is-a-t-shaped-developer-and-why-you-should-be-one-e87293e4bb84"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">T-Shaped Developer</a
        >
        mindset, and I direct my learnings for that. I want to know enough so I can
        create any application, "from idea to production".
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        I have a strong interest in topics related with Engineering best
        practices like CI/CD, DevOps, Testing and automation.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
